<DOC><DOCNO> AP900512-0047 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-12-90 0735EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Lebanon     05-12 0125</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Lebanon,0127</SECOND><HEAD>Christians Fight in Lebanon, Four Wounded</HEAD><DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Rival Christian forces today foughtgunbattles in east Beirut and hills overlooking the coastal highwaynorth of the capital, and four civilians were wounded, police said.   Rebel Gen. Michel Aoun's command and Christian warlord SamirGeagea's Lebanese Forces militia blamed each other for the clashesin east Beirut's Badaro district and the bluffs above the Dog Riverhighway tunnel.   The fighting kept all roads blocked for a fifth straight daybetween the Aoun-controlled Metn province and the rest of Lebanon'sChristian enclave under Geagea's authority, police said.   Since the battle for control of the 310-square-mile Christianenclave broke out Jan. 30, a total of 930 people have been killedand 2,580 wounded.</TEXT></DOC>